<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-03-29T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-03-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 PW/3–2445: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-29T20:00:00-04:00">March
                                        29, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1242. Your 1425, March 24. The French are aware that by March 24 some
                                help had been dropped to their troops in Indo-China. We are trying
                                to get more specific information.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>